Package: actogrammr
Type: Package
Title: Read in Activity Data and Plot Actograms
Version: 0.2.1
Authors@R: person("Robert", "Corty", email = "rcorty@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Read in activity measurements from standard file formats
  used by circadian rhythm researchers, currently only 'ClockLab' format,
  and process and plot the data.  The central type of plot is the 'actogram',
  as first described by MS Johnson, in his 1926 paper in the Journal of Mammalogy 
  entitled "Activity and distribution of certain wild mice in relation to biotic communities".
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 6.0.1
Suggests: testthat,
    covr
Imports: dplyr,
    ggplot2,
    lubridate,
    readr,
    tidyr
